  <li>On the same note, donâ€™t email someone asking to pick their brain about something. â€œBrain pickingâ€ meetings are extremely exhausting because they donâ€™t have a concrete goal and you spend most of the time trying to figure it out. Usually theyâ€™re a sign that the person emailing isnâ€™t really sure what they want, they just want to meet in person.</li>
